1
00:00:10.956 --> 00:00:12.361  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sell at 20.

2
00:00:12.115 --> 00:00:13.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is that a joke?

3
00:00:13.595 --> 00:00:15.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do I look like I'm joking?

4
00:00:16.354 --> 00:00:17.514  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

5
00:00:21.112 --> 00:00:22.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She has him.

6
00:00:22.473 --> 00:00:24.752  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-She's down 50 strips.
-Not for long.

7
00:00:25.231 --> 00:00:26.871  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What makes you so sure?

8
00:00:27.311 --> 00:00:29.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, Jadzia's playing a very deep game.

9
00:00:30.300 --> 00:00:32.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Her strategy will become
apparent any moment now.

10
00:00:32.709 --> 00:00:33.989  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I see.

11
00:00:35.189 --> 00:00:39.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You have absolutely no idea
how this game is played, do you?

12
00:00:40.907 --> 00:00:42.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-No.
-( chuckles )

13
00:00:42.426 --> 00:00:44.865  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I have developed
a new appreciation for it.

14
00:00:44.946 --> 00:00:47.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Oh? Since when?
-Since I married a Tongo player.

15
00:00:48.464 --> 00:00:50.463  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But one thing I am certain about--

16
00:00:50.544 --> 00:00:52.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She will defeat the Ferengi bartender.

17
00:00:52.904 --> 00:00:55.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know about that.
Quark's on a roll.

18
00:00:55.542 --> 00:00:59.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In the last month,
he's won 206 straight games.

19
00:01:01.341 --> 00:01:03.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Would you care to make
a wager on the outcome?

20
00:01:03.700 --> 00:01:06.339  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I wouldn't want to bet
against a man's wife.

21
00:01:06.419 --> 00:01:09.178  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Well, if you are afraid--
-Name your stakes.

22
00:01:09.938 --> 00:01:13.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
One bottle of bloodwine
against one bottle of scotch whiskey.

23
00:01:13.377 --> 00:01:14.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done.

24
00:01:16.616 --> 00:01:19.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A sale at 50 and a purchase at 100.

25
00:01:21.734 --> 00:01:24.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Pretty big talk for
a lady who's lost 50 strips.

26
00:01:25.136 --> 00:01:27.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you afraid I can't cover my bets?

27
00:01:27.931 --> 00:01:28.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Perish the thought!

28
00:01:28.253 --> 00:01:31.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just hate to kick
somebody when they're down.

29
00:01:31.252 --> 00:01:34.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll buy at 100... and confront.

30
00:01:35.651 --> 00:01:38.649  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, if you're gonna kick me,
I'm gonna have to kick back.

31
00:01:38.729 --> 00:01:40.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: unbelievable.

32
00:01:40.209 --> 00:01:41.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( exclaims in native langauge )

33
00:01:43.168 --> 00:01:45.847  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I like my bloodwine
very young and very sweet.

34
00:01:46.927 --> 00:01:49.326  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is he a friend of yours?
-Just a fan.

35
00:01:49.846 --> 00:01:52.725  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid I'm going to have
to disappoint all your fans.

36
00:01:55.285 --> 00:01:56.564  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A full consortium?

37
00:01:56.644 --> 00:01:58.483  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
207.

38
00:01:58.564 --> 00:02:01.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
A single malt,
preferably something from the highlands.

39
00:02:02.202 --> 00:02:03.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will need some time.

40
00:02:03.722 --> 00:02:05.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, your credit's good.

41
00:02:08.520 --> 00:02:11.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoo, 207 straight.

42
00:02:11.798 --> 00:02:13.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
QUARK: 36 strips of gold press latinum.

43
00:02:16.399 --> 00:02:18.558  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Did you lose a bet?
-It is of no consequence.

44
00:02:18.637 --> 00:02:20.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry about that.

45
00:02:23.516 --> 00:02:27.275  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would rather lose a bet on you
than win on someone else.

46
00:02:27.355 --> 00:02:29.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh, good response.

47
00:02:37.352 --> 00:02:39.471  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Are you still running
that drill tomorrow afternoon?

48
00:02:39.551 --> 00:02:41.715  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was planning to. Why?

49
00:02:41.151 --> 00:02:43.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because I wanted to recalibrate
the external sensors

50
00:02:43.710 --> 00:02:46.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
before the night watch comes on duty.

51
00:02:46.988 --> 00:02:49.429  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We should be done by 1600 hours.

52
00:02:49.508 --> 00:02:51.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I think that'll work.

53
00:02:52.507 --> 00:02:56.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, the <i>Sutherland </i>is going to
be here the day after tomorrow and...

54
00:03:12.701 --> 00:03:14.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You were saying?
-Nothing.

55
00:03:20.259 --> 00:03:22.985  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't feel like talking anymore.

56
00:03:42.933 --> 00:03:43.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-( beep )
<i>-Kira to Worf.</i>

57
00:03:52.169 --> 00:03:53.409  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf here.

58
00:03:53.489 --> 00:03:56.489  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
KIRA:<i> Sorry to bother you, Commander,</i>
<i>but I need to see you and Jadzia</i>

59
00:03:56.128 --> 00:03:58.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>in the Captain's office, immediately.</i>

60
00:03:58.208 --> 00:03:59.687  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're on our way.

61
00:04:07.365 --> 00:04:09.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia... Get up.

62
00:04:09.484 --> 00:04:10.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm coming!

63
00:04:11.483 --> 00:04:12.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey!

64
00:04:13.283 --> 00:04:15.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have a lot of time,
so I'll get right to it.

65
00:04:15.803 --> 00:04:17.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
For the last two months,

66
00:04:17.362 --> 00:04:19.921  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet has been receiving
military intelligence

67
00:04:20.151 --> 00:04:21.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
from a Cardassian operative.

68
00:04:21.600 --> 00:04:23.800  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That operative has now sent
an emergency signal

69
00:04:23.880 --> 00:04:27.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
indicating he needs to speak to someone
in a face-to-face conversation.

70
00:04:27.719 --> 00:04:28.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
In 13 hours,

71
00:04:28.998 --> 00:04:31.238  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
he'll beam an encrypted
subspace transmission

72
00:04:31.318 --> 00:04:33.477  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to these coordinates in the badlands.

73
00:04:33.557 --> 00:04:35.117  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who is the operative?

74
00:04:35.196 --> 00:04:37.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Intelligence told me that
his name is Lasaran,

75
00:04:37.876 --> 00:04:39.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But that's all they'll say about him.

76
00:04:39.835 --> 00:04:43.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They did emphasize several times that
he is very important to them

77
00:04:43.554 --> 00:04:46.394  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and that we should send someone
to the badlands as soon as possible.

78
00:04:47.335 --> 00:04:49.113  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, with the <i>Defiant </i>gone,

79
00:04:49.192 --> 00:04:52.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and most of the runabouts off on exercises
with the Ninth Fleet...

80
00:04:52.631 --> 00:04:54.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We just volunteered for
a trip to the badlands.

81
00:04:54.711 --> 00:04:55.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Afraid so.

82
00:04:55.870 --> 00:04:58.550  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The <i>Shenandoah's </i>prepped
and ready to go on landing pad "A."

83
00:04:58.629 --> 00:04:59.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

84
00:07:11.349 --> 00:07:12.790  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-No.
-No?

85
00:07:12.869 --> 00:07:14.509  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
No, I'm not going to spend two weeks

86
00:07:14.589 --> 00:07:17.228  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
hiking across Vulcan's forge
in the middle of their summer.

87
00:07:17.308 --> 00:07:19.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I thought you always
wanted to see the forge.

88
00:07:19.388 --> 00:07:22.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
See it, yes. Honeymoon there, no.

89
00:07:22.466 --> 00:07:24.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Well, there's a mountain-climbing
expedition on Andor

90
00:07:24.386 --> 00:07:25.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
that caught my attention.

91
00:07:25.426 --> 00:07:28.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Worf... My love...

92
00:07:28.185 --> 00:07:29.704  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
Let me make this very clear.

93
00:07:29.784 --> 00:07:31.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I do not want to spend my honeymoon

94
00:07:31.984 --> 00:07:35.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
climbing, hiking, sweating, bleeding,
or suffering in any way.

95
00:07:36.742 --> 00:07:38.822  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-All right, what do you want?
-Room service.

96
00:07:38.901 --> 00:07:39.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
-Room service?
-Room service.

97
00:07:39.981 --> 00:07:41.617  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want to be pampered.

98
00:07:41.141 --> 00:07:43.340  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want a staff to cater to our every whim.

99
00:07:43.420 --> 00:07:46.260  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want to be embarrassed
by the size of our room.

100
00:07:46.339 --> 00:07:48.859  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
I want a balcony with a view
that would make you want

101
00:07:48.938 --> 00:07:51.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
to break down and cry
from the sheer beauty of it all.

102
00:07:51.618 --> 00:07:54.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
And I don't want to spend
one moment of our honeymoon

103
00:07:55.173 --> 00:07:56.376  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
suffering from anything

104
00:07:56.456 --> 00:07:59.856  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:10.00% 
except guilt about
our complete self-indulgence.

105
00:08:00.575 --> 00:08:01.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Risa.

106
00:08:01.615 --> 00:08:02.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not this time.

107
00:08:04.948 --> 00:08:06.535  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome to Casperia Prime,

108
00:08:06.134 --> 00:08:08.893  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
the vacation capital
of the Horvarian cluster.

109
00:08:12.412 --> 00:08:14.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have been planning this all along.

110
00:08:14.810 --> 00:08:17.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, it seemed fair.
You did plan the wedding.

111
00:08:18.850 --> 00:08:20.329  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Very well. Room service.

112
00:08:20.409 --> 00:08:22.528  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Really?
-Really.

113
00:08:22.609 --> 00:08:23.808  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that was easy.

114
00:08:24.687 --> 00:08:26.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you want to fight over it?

115
00:08:26.288 --> 00:08:27.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. It's just...

116
00:08:27.887 --> 00:08:30.406  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I didn't expect you
to surrender so quickly.

117
00:08:30.486 --> 00:08:32.607  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Surrender?
-Bad word.

118
00:08:32.856 --> 00:08:33.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Very bad.
-OK.

119
00:08:33.845 --> 00:08:37.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But you have to admit you've been
unusually...accommodating lately.

120
00:08:38.644 --> 00:08:39.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What is wrong with that?

121
00:08:39.963 --> 00:08:41.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nothing. It's just...

122
00:08:41.962 --> 00:08:43.163  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Unusual.

123
00:08:43.242 --> 00:08:44.402  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you feeling all right?

124
00:08:44.482 --> 00:08:46.121  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am a married man.

125
00:08:46.761 --> 00:08:50.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have to make certain...
adjustments in my lifestyle.

126
00:08:50.400 --> 00:08:52.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Adjustments?

127
00:08:52.239 --> 00:08:54.279  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, you're practically easygoing.

128
00:08:54.359 --> 00:08:55.718  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's next, a sense of humor?

129
00:08:55.798 --> 00:08:57.717  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have a sense of humor.

130
00:08:58.398 --> 00:09:00.997  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
On the <i>Enterprise,</i>
I was considered to be quite amusing.

131
00:09:01.397 --> 00:09:03.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that must've been one dull ship.

132
00:09:04.715 --> 00:09:05.955  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is a joke!

133
00:09:06.360 --> 00:09:07.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I get it.

134
00:09:07.235 --> 00:09:09.154  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is not funny, but I get it.

135
00:09:09.234 --> 00:09:11.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know if I can
get used to the new you.

136
00:09:11.914 --> 00:09:13.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's kind of eerie.

137
00:09:13.353 --> 00:09:16.353  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your problem is
you cannot accept change.

138
00:09:16.432 --> 00:09:19.722  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I can't accept change?
-That is correct.

139
00:09:19.151 --> 00:09:20.631  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you've got to be kidding.

140
00:09:20.711 --> 00:09:22.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've changed bodies six times, Worf.

141
00:09:22.911 --> 00:09:25.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but you are still
very set in your ways.

142
00:09:25.749 --> 00:09:27.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And look who's talking.

143
00:09:27.669 --> 00:09:31.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I do not have to sleep
on the same side of the bed every night,

144
00:09:31.428 --> 00:09:34.547  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or brush my hair exactly 50 strokes
every night,

145
00:09:34.627 --> 00:09:37.268  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or eat the same thing
for breakfast every day,

146
00:09:37.106 --> 00:09:39.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
or read the last page of the book
before the beginning,

147
00:09:39.666 --> 00:09:41.625  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-or lift up--
-I get the point.

148
00:09:42.265 --> 00:09:45.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't know how you can live
with someone so monotonous.

149
00:09:46.183 --> 00:09:47.423  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is not easy.

150
00:09:49.982 --> 00:09:51.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was a joke.

151
00:09:53.181 --> 00:09:57.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This is going to be
a very, very long trip.

152
00:10:05.579 --> 00:10:06.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door chimes )

153
00:10:06.497 --> 00:10:07.737  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come in.

154
00:10:08.776 --> 00:10:10.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not dressed.

155
00:10:10.776 --> 00:10:12.976  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Is it time?
-1700 on the dot.

156
00:10:13.558 --> 00:10:14.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have the holosuite
for the next three hours,

157
00:10:14.494 --> 00:10:15.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we're going to
need every minute of it.

158
00:10:15.535 --> 00:10:17.774  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Three British agents have disappeared
in West Berlin.

159
00:10:17.854 --> 00:10:21.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Now, M.I. Five suspect
the Soviets were involved of course.

160
00:10:21.253 --> 00:10:23.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
However, the Americans
have intercepted a, uh...

161
00:10:23.612 --> 00:10:25.371  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you doing with a Tongo wheel?

162
00:10:25.452 --> 00:10:27.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm brushing up on my game.

163
00:10:27.291 --> 00:10:29.170  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You play Tongo?
-Sure.

164
00:10:30.130 --> 00:10:31.850  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, I used to.

165
00:10:33.130 --> 00:10:35.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
That is, I played the game once,
a long time ago,

166
00:10:35.648 --> 00:10:39.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with a Ferengi privateer
and a Romulan mercenary.

167
00:10:39.527 --> 00:10:40.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fascinating.

168
00:10:40.647 --> 00:10:44.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Anyway, the Americans have intercepted
a series of messages from Istanbul

169
00:10:44.326 --> 00:10:45.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to a remote island in the South Pacific

170
00:10:46.455 --> 00:10:47.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-which might indicate--
-Let's play a hand.

171
00:10:47.205 --> 00:10:48.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles...

172
00:10:48.244 --> 00:10:49.604  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Just one hand.
-Why?

173
00:10:49.685 --> 00:10:50.804  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need the practice.

174
00:10:50.884 --> 00:10:52.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

175
00:10:52.324 --> 00:10:54.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want to beat Quark.

176
00:10:54.283 --> 00:10:55.362  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good luck.

177
00:10:55.443 --> 00:10:57.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Luck has nothing to do with it.

178
00:10:57.282 --> 00:11:00.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Tongo is a game of strategy
and calculated risk.

179
00:11:00.561 --> 00:11:01.561  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't even know the rules.

180
00:11:01.641 --> 00:11:03.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, here.

181
00:11:03.281 --> 00:11:05.797  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right, let's play. I'll deal.

182
00:11:06.359 --> 00:11:09.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: <i>Shenandoah log: Stardate 51597.2.</i>

183
00:11:10.786 --> 00:11:12.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>We have arrived </i>
<i>at the designated coordinates</i>

184
00:11:12.117 --> 00:11:15.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>near the badlands and are</i>
<i>awaiting the transmission from Lasaran.</i>

185
00:11:17.636 --> 00:11:18.876  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: This is it.

186
00:11:18.955 --> 00:11:20.875  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
A very sophisticated encryption matrix.

187
00:11:21.315 --> 00:11:22.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoever he is, he's good.

188
00:11:25.833 --> 00:11:26.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Who are you?</i>

189
00:11:26.833 --> 00:11:29.753  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Commander Worf. This is Commander Dax.

190
00:11:29.832 --> 00:11:32.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet Intelligence has sent us here
to receive your transmission.

191
00:11:33.321 --> 00:11:34.714  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>A Klingon.</i>

192
00:11:34.951 --> 00:11:37.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Why did they have to send a Klingon?</i>

193
00:11:37.110 --> 00:11:39.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm a Trill.
Does that make you feel any better?

194
00:11:39.549 --> 00:11:43.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>-Are you trying to be funny?</i>
-Oh, not at all. He's the funny one.

195
00:11:43.388 --> 00:11:46.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What is it you want?
<i>-We'll get to that in a minute.</i>

196
00:11:46.107 --> 00:11:48.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>First, I have something </i>
<i>that you want, badly...</i>

197
00:11:48.907 --> 00:11:50.506  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Information on the Founders.</i>

198
00:11:50.786 --> 00:11:53.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I know how many of them</i>
<i>there are in the Alpha Quadrant,</i>

199
00:11:53.385 --> 00:11:55.465  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>where they are, and what they're doing.</i>

200
00:11:55.544 --> 00:11:58.240  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-We're listening.
<i>-I'm sure you are.</i>

201
00:11:58.104 --> 00:11:59.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Now let's talk about what I want.</i>

202
00:11:59.703 --> 00:12:01.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I want out, now.</i>

203
00:12:01.423 --> 00:12:02.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You want to defect.

204
00:12:02.822 --> 00:12:04.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>The Vorta advisor here </i>
<i>is getting suspicious...</i>

205
00:12:05.622 --> 00:12:06.261  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Asking questions,</i>

206
00:12:06.342 --> 00:12:08.740  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>making a lot of routine </i>
<i>security checks in my section.</i>

207
00:12:08.821 --> 00:12:10.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I can't stay here any longer.</i>

208
00:12:10.700 --> 00:12:11.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: Very well.

209
00:12:11.780 --> 00:12:13.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We will relay your message
to Starfleet Intelligence

210
00:12:14.198 --> 00:12:15.499  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they will arrange to bring you out.

211
00:12:15.578 --> 00:12:17.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I can't wait for them </i>
<i>to make arrangements.</i>

212
00:12:17.498 --> 00:12:21.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>In 15 minutes, I am leaving here</i>
<i>for the Dominion base on Soukara,</i>

213
00:12:21.577 --> 00:12:23.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>and I have a feeling </i>
<i>this is going to be the last time</i>

214
00:12:23.576 --> 00:12:25.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>that they let me leave Cardassia Prime.</i>

215
00:12:25.536 --> 00:12:28.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>So, I need to take advantage </i>
<i>of this opportunity.</i>

216
00:12:29.550 --> 00:12:31.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Soukara is inside
Dominion-controlled space.

217
00:12:31.534 --> 00:12:35.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It will not be easy to make a rendezvous
near that planet without being detected.

218
00:12:35.213 --> 00:12:37.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Don't work your brain too hard, Klingon.</i>

219
00:12:37.372 --> 00:12:38.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>I've taken care of everything.</i>

220
00:12:39.116 --> 00:12:42.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Three days from now </i>
<i>at exactly 1730 hours local time,</i>

221
00:12:42.970 --> 00:12:45.609  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I will leave the base </i>
<i>and walk into the jungle.</i>

222
00:12:45.690 --> 00:12:48.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>It'll be at least two days</i>
<i>before they know I'm missing.</i>

223
00:12:48.888 --> 00:12:52.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>All you have to do </i>
<i>is get me off the planet.</i>

224
00:12:52.881 --> 00:12:55.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Now, there are transporter scramblers </i>
<i>protecting Soukara</i>

225
00:12:55.446 --> 00:12:57.126  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>so you can't beam me aboard your ship.</i>

226
00:12:57.206 --> 00:13:01.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You're going to have to land</i>
<i>and meet me at a rendezvous point on foot.</i>

227
00:13:01.685 --> 00:13:04.447  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I am sending you all </i>
<i>the information you'll need</i>

228
00:13:04.124 --> 00:13:06.923  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>to avoid the Dominion sensors </i>
<i>on the ground.</i>

229
00:13:07.363 --> 00:13:08.803  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Follow my instructions.</i>

230
00:13:08.882 --> 00:13:12.682  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Meet me at this rendezvous point</i>
<i>and have a ship waiting.</i>

231
00:13:14.416 --> 00:13:16.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We've got the information.
It looks pretty thorough.

232
00:13:16.681 --> 00:13:18.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will need time to study these plans.

233
00:13:18.680 --> 00:13:20.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>You haven't been listening. </i>
<i>I don't have time.</i>

234
00:13:20.919 --> 00:13:23.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>Once I leave here, </i>
<i>I can't contact you again.</i>

235
00:13:23.438 --> 00:13:25.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>I have to know if you're</i>
<i>going to be there or not,</i>

236
00:13:25.757 --> 00:13:27.357  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>and I have to know now!</i>

237
00:13:29.996 --> 00:13:31.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We will be there.

238
00:13:32.515 --> 00:13:34.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>How far I've fallen... </i>( sighs )

239
00:13:34.995 --> 00:13:37.434  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Risking my life on the word of a Klingon.</i>

240
00:13:38.474 --> 00:13:40.873  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Three days. Don't be late.</i>

241
00:13:55.349 --> 00:13:58.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
All right.
I'll buy at 30 with sales at 35.

242
00:13:59.676 --> 00:14:02.467  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Buy at 35, sell at 150
and index the margin at 10%.

243
00:14:02.946 --> 00:14:05.346  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Index the margin?
-Miles, give it up.

244
00:14:05.426 --> 00:14:07.825  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-This just isn't your game.
-We'll see about that.

245
00:14:07.905 --> 00:14:08.905  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

246
00:14:09.784 --> 00:14:10.984  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

247
00:14:12.703 --> 00:14:13.943  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do you realize

248
00:14:14.232 --> 00:14:17.302  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that Quark has won
207 straight games of Tongo?

249
00:14:17.382 --> 00:14:18.462  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So?

250
00:14:18.541 --> 00:14:19.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, someone has to beat him.

251
00:14:19.821 --> 00:14:21.461  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And that someone is you?

252
00:14:21.541 --> 00:14:22.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Why not?

253
00:14:22.861 --> 00:14:25.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, for one thing, you can't play Tongo.

254
00:14:25.620 --> 00:14:26.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

255
00:14:27.739 --> 00:14:29.138  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans ) Damn!

256
00:14:29.219 --> 00:14:31.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Had enough?
-Not by a long shot.

257
00:14:31.938 --> 00:14:34.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Miles, at this rate,
it's going to take you another 20 years

258
00:14:34.537 --> 00:14:35.897  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
to be ready to take on Quark.

259
00:14:35.976 --> 00:14:37.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
One more.

260
00:14:37.965 --> 00:14:39.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
( sighs ) Why are you
so determined to beat him?

261
00:14:39.896 --> 00:14:41.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-It's the challenge.
-A challenge?

262
00:14:41.935 --> 00:14:43.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Isn't it enough?

263
00:14:43.294 --> 00:14:44.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I mean, why do you think
I became an engineer, eh?

264
00:14:45.542 --> 00:14:46.614  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The challenge.

265
00:14:46.693 --> 00:14:49.292  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What do you think's kept me
kayaking down the same river

266
00:14:49.373 --> 00:14:51.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
week after week for the last seven years?

267
00:14:51.851 --> 00:14:53.531  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The challenge.

268
00:14:53.612 --> 00:14:55.730  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Why would I keep playing darts
against somebody

269
00:14:55.811 --> 00:14:59.210  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with a genetically engineered
hand/eye coordination, huh?

270
00:14:59.289 --> 00:15:01.448  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-The challenge.
-Exactly.

271
00:15:03.848 --> 00:15:05.727  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I have to do something
to keep my mind off the fact

272
00:15:05.808 --> 00:15:08.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that Keiko's been away
for the last six months.

273
00:15:10.326 --> 00:15:11.486  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hold on.

274
00:15:12.565 --> 00:15:14.805  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Maybe I can't beat Quark...

275
00:15:15.565 --> 00:15:16.964  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But you can.

276
00:15:17.764 --> 00:15:20.123  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and that genetically
engineered brain of yours.

277
00:15:20.204 --> 00:15:22.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Me? I've only just learned
how to play the game.

278
00:15:22.283 --> 00:15:24.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, in about 10 seconds flat!

279
00:15:25.522 --> 00:15:26.922  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can do it, Julian.

280
00:15:27.161 --> 00:15:28.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We can beat him.

281
00:15:28.480 --> 00:15:29.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"We"?

282
00:15:30.440 --> 00:15:31.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're talking about me.

283
00:15:31.920 --> 00:15:34.999  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yeah, well, you're good at calculation
but a little weak on strategy.

284
00:15:35.399 --> 00:15:37.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll be your coach.
-No, thank you.

285
00:15:37.758 --> 00:15:39.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Think of it as a challenge.

286
00:15:39.518 --> 00:15:41.237  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's your obsession, Miles, not mine.

287
00:15:41.317 --> 00:15:42.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do it for the latinum.

288
00:15:42.557 --> 00:15:43.716  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nice try.

289
00:15:43.797 --> 00:15:47.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Do it for the satisfaction
of the look on Quark's face

290
00:15:47.475 --> 00:15:51.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
when he's beaten at a game of Tongo
by a lowly "hu-man."

291
00:15:52.234 --> 00:15:53.273  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Deal the cards.

292
00:16:02.551 --> 00:16:04.430  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are approaching the Soukara system.

293
00:16:04.510 --> 00:16:05.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Stand by to bring us out of warp.

294
00:16:05.950 --> 00:16:07.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now.

295
00:16:08.669 --> 00:16:10.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There is an asteroid field directly ahead.

296
00:16:10.428 --> 00:16:11.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's what we want.

297
00:16:11.507 --> 00:16:13.828  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The Dominion's sensor grid
in the system has three gaps

298
00:16:13.907 --> 00:16:15.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and they're all in that asteroid field.

299
00:16:20.985 --> 00:16:22.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: Want me to slow down?

300
00:16:22.305 --> 00:16:24.464  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, unless you think you should.

301
00:16:24.544 --> 00:16:26.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not at all. In fact, we could go faster.

302
00:16:26.503 --> 00:16:27.903  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
By all means.

303
00:16:28.423 --> 00:16:30.382  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ooh! A man after my own heart.

304
00:16:44.338 --> 00:16:46.182  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Most impressive.

305
00:16:46.978 --> 00:16:48.816  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Nothing that any
300-year-old pilot couldn't do.

306
00:16:49.376 --> 00:16:51.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We are being scanned from the surface.

307
00:16:51.616 --> 00:16:53.735  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
JADZIA: Taking evasive maneuvers.

308
00:16:53.815 --> 00:16:54.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did they get a fix on us?

309
00:16:55.554 --> 00:16:56.455  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: I do not think so.

310
00:16:56.534 --> 00:16:59.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
JADZIA: Good. We've come too long a way
just to get shot down.

311
00:16:59.334 --> 00:17:02.173  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you take the helm,
I'll scan the surface for a landing site.

312
00:17:03.852 --> 00:17:05.732  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's the base...

313
00:17:05.811 --> 00:17:07.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The rendezvous point...

314
00:17:08.916 --> 00:17:10.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the Dominion sensor perimeter.

315
00:17:10.810 --> 00:17:14.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's a valley about 20 kilometers
north of the rendezvous point.

316
00:17:14.969 --> 00:17:16.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's a long way to go
on foot in the jungle,

317
00:17:16.329 --> 00:17:19.328  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I don't think we can risk taking
the ship any closer to their sensors.

318
00:17:19.407 --> 00:17:20.487  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Agreed.

319
00:17:30.844 --> 00:17:32.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have less than two days
to reach the rendezvous point.

320
00:17:32.644 --> 00:17:35.203  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
About 10 kilometers a day,
that shouldn't be too bad.

321
00:17:35.282 --> 00:17:37.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Do not underestimate the task ahead.

322
00:17:37.362 --> 00:17:40.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We still have to penetrate the sensor grid
and avoid the Dominion patrols.

323
00:17:40.322 --> 00:17:41.761  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) I know,

324
00:17:41.841 --> 00:17:44.120  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
find a man in the middle
of an alien jungle,

325
00:17:44.200 --> 00:17:45.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
then walk him out without getting caught.

326
00:17:45.559 --> 00:17:46.839  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Piece of cake.

327
00:17:46.920 --> 00:17:49.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Ready?
-After you.

328
00:18:03.235 --> 00:18:04.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
OK.

329
00:18:04.634 --> 00:18:05.993  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Go to 25 joules.

330
00:18:13.831 --> 00:18:14.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
WORF: 25 joules.

331
00:18:17.990 --> 00:18:19.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Done.

332
00:18:19.110 --> 00:18:20.510  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's it. We're linked.

333
00:18:23.509 --> 00:18:24.548  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Here, check my work.

334
00:18:26.587 --> 00:18:28.867  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dominion encryption lockouts bypassed,

335
00:18:28.947 --> 00:18:31.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
tricorder link to their sensor grids,

336
00:18:31.106 --> 00:18:32.706  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
life signs masked.

337
00:18:32.786 --> 00:18:33.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nicely done.

338
00:18:33.865 --> 00:18:35.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

339
00:18:38.584 --> 00:18:42.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of course, our tricorders
will be useless from now on.

340
00:18:42.143 --> 00:18:43.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There you go again,

341
00:18:43.342 --> 00:18:45.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
looking for the cloud
in the silver lining.

342
00:18:45.341 --> 00:18:47.662  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I am not complaining.

343
00:18:47.741 --> 00:18:49.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I look forward to walking
through the jungle

344
00:18:49.381 --> 00:18:52.420  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
without a map
and no idea of what lies ahead.

345
00:18:53.195 --> 00:18:55.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, the funny thing is you probably are.

346
00:19:01.417 --> 00:19:03.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a Ferengi-only game, gentlemen.

347
00:19:03.856 --> 00:19:05.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You let Dax play.

348
00:19:05.416 --> 00:19:08.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's an exception, the only exception.

349
00:19:08.335 --> 00:19:09.654  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're afraid I'll clean you out.

350
00:19:09.735 --> 00:19:13.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'm afraid you'll embarrass yourself
and ruin the game for the rest of us.

351
00:19:13.173 --> 00:19:15.929  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I can keep up.

352
00:19:15.173 --> 00:19:17.413  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The question is, can you keep up with me?

353
00:19:17.492 --> 00:19:19.611  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't try and scare me
with that genetically engineered

354
00:19:19.692 --> 00:19:21.810  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
intellect of yours, Doctor.

355
00:19:21.891 --> 00:19:24.250  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tongo is more than just number crunching.

356
00:19:24.330 --> 00:19:27.102  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have yet to create the computer
that can master this game.

357
00:19:27.898 --> 00:19:29.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then you shouldn't have
anything to worry about.

358
00:19:29.768 --> 00:19:33.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You realize we are not playing for drinks.

359
00:19:33.607 --> 00:19:36.474  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is a high stakes game.

360
00:19:36.727 --> 00:19:38.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We came to play.

361
00:19:39.765 --> 00:19:41.454  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Gentlemen?

362
00:19:41.605 --> 00:19:42.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

363
00:19:44.364 --> 00:19:45.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
All right.

364
00:19:45.764 --> 00:19:49.309  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The buy-in is five strips,
and you're dealing.

365
00:19:52.482 --> 00:19:55.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You better get off to a fast start.

366
00:19:55.321 --> 00:19:57.280  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They won't know what hit them.

367
00:20:02.519 --> 00:20:04.918  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Buy at 300, sell at 350.

368
00:20:08.237 --> 00:20:11.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You're a quick study, Doctor.
I'll give you that.

369
00:20:11.157 --> 00:20:13.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean quick for a "hu-man,"
don't you, Quark?

370
00:20:13.316 --> 00:20:16.114  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would never say anything
so distasteful during a game.

371
00:20:16.195 --> 00:20:17.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, you'd wait until it was over.

372
00:20:18.314 --> 00:20:19.833  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Of course.

373
00:20:19.914 --> 00:20:21.734  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

374
00:20:23.712 --> 00:20:25.431  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax was a quick study too.

375
00:20:25.512 --> 00:20:27.551  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She told me it only took her two weeks
to win her first match.

376
00:20:27.631 --> 00:20:28.870  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's practically unheard of.

377
00:20:28.951 --> 00:20:31.110  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dax specializes in the unexpected.

378
00:20:31.190 --> 00:20:33.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Still buying at 300, selling at four.

379
00:20:34.869 --> 00:20:37.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'd like to index the margin at 20%.

380
00:20:37.508 --> 00:20:39.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Interesting.

381
00:20:39.427 --> 00:20:42.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She certainly did the unexpected
when she married Commander Boring.

382
00:20:42.467 --> 00:20:43.826  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's for sure.

383
00:20:43.907 --> 00:20:46.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When they first started seeing each other,
I thought,

384
00:20:46.145 --> 00:20:49.249  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"This can't last. I give it two months."

385
00:20:50.144 --> 00:20:52.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll buy at 400...

386
00:20:52.463 --> 00:20:53.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And sell at five.

387
00:20:54.344 --> 00:20:55.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had the same thought.

388
00:20:55.742 --> 00:20:57.582  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Although, to tell you the truth,
I only gave it a month.

389
00:20:57.662 --> 00:20:59.620  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

390
00:20:59.142 --> 00:21:01.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's a real heart-breaker, that one.

391
00:21:02.620 --> 00:21:04.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That she is.

392
00:21:04.380 --> 00:21:08.259  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Leverage the buy-in and sell at 550.

393
00:21:09.659 --> 00:21:11.418  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know...

394
00:21:11.498 --> 00:21:14.817  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You go through a lot of ups and downs
in my business.

395
00:21:15.577 --> 00:21:19.166  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There are days when the profits are down,
and the customers are scarce,

396
00:21:19.962 --> 00:21:22.655  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and you think you'll never see
another strip of latinum again,

397
00:21:23.935 --> 00:21:26.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And then, Jadzia comes in...

398
00:21:27.538 --> 00:21:29.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And flashes that smile of hers.

399
00:21:30.373 --> 00:21:33.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Suddenly things
don't seem so bad after all.

400
00:21:33.412 --> 00:21:35.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know exactly what you mean.

401
00:21:35.811 --> 00:21:39.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You know,
sometimes she walks past the infirmary,

402
00:21:39.170 --> 00:21:42.169  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and all she has to do is wink,
and somehow, that...

403
00:21:42.249 --> 00:21:44.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
makes my whole day look a little brighter.

404
00:21:44.890 --> 00:21:45.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Focus, Julian. Focus.

405
00:21:46.288 --> 00:21:47.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Shh!

406
00:21:48.207 --> 00:21:52.485  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'll, uh, buy that 550, and...

407
00:21:53.365 --> 00:21:54.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Index the exchange at 10.

408
00:21:55.485 --> 00:21:57.164  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And now she's married.

409
00:21:57.245 --> 00:21:58.848  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Married.

410
00:21:58.484 --> 00:21:59.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Out of reach.

411
00:22:01.363 --> 00:22:02.843  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm converting my reserves...

412
00:22:03.642 --> 00:22:05.241  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And selling at 600.

413
00:22:06.842 --> 00:22:08.601  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know what's really sad?

414
00:22:08.681 --> 00:22:11.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What really keeps me awake at night?

415
00:22:11.280 --> 00:22:13.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's out of reach because we let her go.

416
00:22:15.918 --> 00:22:17.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, I suppose so...

417
00:22:18.787 --> 00:22:19.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But some things just weren't meant to be.

418
00:22:21.956 --> 00:22:22.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Evade.

419
00:22:22.997 --> 00:22:24.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Julian!

420
00:22:24.316 --> 00:22:25.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you sure you want to--

421
00:22:25.716 --> 00:22:28.755  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Chief! Please. You know the rules.

422
00:22:28.834 --> 00:22:30.354  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No coaching during a round.

423
00:22:34.993 --> 00:22:36.473  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're probably right.

424
00:22:38.912 --> 00:22:41.311  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But what if that's
a convenient rationalization?

425
00:22:42.351 --> 00:22:46.829  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if deep down in our heart of hearts,
we both know she's something unique...

426
00:22:46.909 --> 00:22:48.988  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Something we may never see again,

427
00:22:49.694 --> 00:22:50.748  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
a chance at true happiness?

428
00:22:50.828 --> 00:22:53.427  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And we let her slip through our fingers.

429
00:22:53.868 --> 00:22:55.947  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What if 50 years from now
we each look back

430
00:22:56.271 --> 00:22:58.705  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and say, "What a fool I was"?

431
00:23:03.104 --> 00:23:04.305  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

432
00:23:05.143 --> 00:23:06.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Doctor?

433
00:23:06.304 --> 00:23:07.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm?

434
00:23:07.583 --> 00:23:08.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Confront.

435
00:23:08.943 --> 00:23:10.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

436
00:23:10.343 --> 00:23:11.742  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry. Um...

437
00:23:13.141 --> 00:23:14.381  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Full consortium.

438
00:23:17.820 --> 00:23:20.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Total monopoly.

439
00:23:20.379 --> 00:23:21.779  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-What?
-( Ferengis snickering )

440
00:23:24.978 --> 00:23:26.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You seem to be out of money.

441
00:23:27.297 --> 00:23:28.457  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Miles?

442
00:23:29.217 --> 00:23:30.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We're busted.

443
00:23:30.296 --> 00:23:31.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks for the game.

444
00:23:31.576 --> 00:23:32.855  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Welcome back anytime.

445
00:23:32.936 --> 00:23:33.815  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
BASHIR: Wait.

446
00:23:33.896 --> 00:23:37.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Quark, did you really mean all that
about Dax...

447
00:23:38.294 --> 00:23:40.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Being my one last chance
for true happiness?

448
00:23:41.573 --> 00:23:47.251  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Doctor, you don't expect me
to show you all my cards, do you?

449
00:23:48.251 --> 00:23:49.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( money rattling )

450
00:23:50.930 --> 00:23:52.930  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) You lost.

451
00:23:53.972 --> 00:23:54.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What ever happened to "we"?

452
00:23:54.210 --> 00:23:58.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We weren't mooning over lost love
with a Ferengi holding a total monopoly.

453
00:23:59.488 --> 00:24:01.367  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You mean all that about Dax
was meant to distract me?

454
00:24:01.447 --> 00:24:02.927  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Obviously.

455
00:24:03.665 --> 00:24:04.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't believe I let him get to me.

456
00:24:05.468 --> 00:24:07.565  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah. Well... Not your fault.

457
00:24:08.925 --> 00:24:12.404  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Genetically engineered or not,
you're still "hu-man."

458
00:24:14.243 --> 00:24:16.162  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( rueful chuckling ) I guess.

459
00:24:16.882 --> 00:24:18.882  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Let's get a drink.
-( groaning )

460
00:24:42.514 --> 00:24:44.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device humming )

461
00:25:02.429 --> 00:25:03.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ow!

462
00:25:56.252 --> 00:25:57.572  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( shivering )

463
00:25:59.531 --> 00:26:02.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, let's not stand on pride, shall we?

464
00:26:02.451 --> 00:26:04.890  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Trills don't like the heat
and Klingons don't like the cold.

465
00:26:04.970 --> 00:26:06.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There's no shame in admitting it.

466
00:26:07.689 --> 00:26:08.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

467
00:26:08.769 --> 00:26:10.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

468
00:26:11.169 --> 00:26:13.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, how are you enjoying your honeymoon?

469
00:26:13.168 --> 00:26:15.207  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you suffering enough?

470
00:26:15.287 --> 00:26:16.686  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Almost.

471
00:26:17.126 --> 00:26:18.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is there anything I can get for you?

472
00:26:20.525 --> 00:26:21.645  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
More pain.

473
00:26:22.164 --> 00:26:23.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less cold.

474
00:26:23.325 --> 00:26:24.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( laughing )

475
00:26:24.844 --> 00:26:26.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know why that's funny, but it is.

476
00:26:27.377 --> 00:26:28.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( animal howling )

477
00:26:29.123 --> 00:26:30.562  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mating call?

478
00:26:30.923 --> 00:26:32.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
500 meters.

479
00:26:33.161 --> 00:26:34.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That way.

480
00:26:34.601 --> 00:26:36.201  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

481
00:26:38.409 --> 00:26:39.680  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well, that didn't take long.

482
00:26:40.360 --> 00:26:42.239  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Less than 300 meters.

483
00:26:42.318 --> 00:26:44.398  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

484
00:26:45.118 --> 00:26:47.517  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) Another happy couple.

485
00:26:52.556 --> 00:26:54.155  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When I was a boy,

486
00:26:54.636 --> 00:26:58.634  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
my father used to take my brother and me
on camping trips in the Ural mountains.

487
00:27:00.394 --> 00:27:04.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Every night, we would listen to the wolves
howling in the distance.

488
00:27:05.432 --> 00:27:07.112  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nikolai was afraid of them,

489
00:27:07.191 --> 00:27:10.470  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but I would lay in my tent for hours,
just listening.

490
00:27:12.950 --> 00:27:16.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I remember being seized by the urge
to just rip off my clothes

491
00:27:16.989 --> 00:27:19.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and run into the night
and live in the forest,

492
00:27:19.388 --> 00:27:22.387  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and become something... wild.

493
00:27:23.906 --> 00:27:25.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling )

494
00:27:28.745 --> 00:27:31.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He must have been rejected.
He's moving away.

495
00:27:32.783 --> 00:27:34.104  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( howling and growling )

496
00:27:34.183 --> 00:27:35.743  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's not happy.

497
00:27:35.823 --> 00:27:36.863  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( twig snaps )

498
00:27:36.942 --> 00:27:38.502  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( growling )

499
00:27:38.582 --> 00:27:40.661  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What? They're getting further away,
aren't they?

500
00:27:40.741 --> 00:27:44.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Yes, but it's because
something is coming.

501
00:27:45.820 --> 00:27:46.860  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And it is close.

502
00:28:00.815 --> 00:28:02.495  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( brush rustling )

503
00:28:14.211 --> 00:28:15.851  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device beeping )

504
00:28:34.325 --> 00:28:35.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( yelling and grunting )

505
00:28:39.244 --> 00:28:41.603  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( strangled gurgling yell )

506
00:28:42.962 --> 00:28:44.202  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

507
00:28:44.282 --> 00:28:45.841  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia!

508
00:28:46.522 --> 00:28:47.961  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

509
00:28:51.720 --> 00:28:53.559  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasping )

510
00:28:55.479 --> 00:28:56.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lie still.

511
00:28:56.759 --> 00:28:58.438  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think I can do that.

512
00:28:59.678 --> 00:29:00.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

513
00:29:00.837 --> 00:29:02.317  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Can I have the good news first?

514
00:29:05.636 --> 00:29:07.515  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No vital organs were damaged.

515
00:29:07.595 --> 00:29:09.594  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Now the bad news?

516
00:29:09.675 --> 00:29:12.274  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The disruptor burst
left an anti-coagulant in your system.

517
00:29:12.834 --> 00:29:15.193  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So you can't stop the bleeding?

518
00:29:15.273 --> 00:29:16.432  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

519
00:29:16.513 --> 00:29:19.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I must not have taken
the whole burst.

520
00:29:19.711 --> 00:29:21.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not hemorrhaging that bad yet.

521
00:29:22.712 --> 00:29:25.390  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Just keep me pumped full of painkillers,
and let's be on our way.

522
00:29:25.470 --> 00:29:26.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Moving could make the bleeding worse.

523
00:29:26.950 --> 00:29:28.869  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Staying here isn't an option.

524
00:29:29.389 --> 00:29:31.908  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Someone's going to come looking for them
when they don't check in,

525
00:29:31.988 --> 00:29:34.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I'd rather take my chances on foot.

526
00:29:34.267 --> 00:29:35.307  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You ready?

527
00:29:37.426 --> 00:29:39.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You ready?
-Ready.

528
00:29:40.145 --> 00:29:41.665  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let's go.

529
00:29:42.185 --> 00:29:43.624  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

530
00:29:58.206 --> 00:29:59.140  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans softly )

531
00:30:07.378 --> 00:30:09.977  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We are still 12 kilometers
from the rendezvous point.

532
00:30:10.568 --> 00:30:11.776  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And only 20 hours left.

533
00:30:12.256 --> 00:30:15.415  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I guess it's time
we stop having so much fun

534
00:30:15.495 --> 00:30:17.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and pick up the pace, huh?

535
00:30:17.974 --> 00:30:19.773  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, more plasma.

536
00:30:19.854 --> 00:30:21.813  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, thanks. I'm full. ( chuckles weakly )

537
00:30:22.772 --> 00:30:25.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Your blood pressure
has dropped another 20%.

538
00:30:25.132 --> 00:30:27.124  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Love that bedside manner.

539
00:30:27.919 --> 00:30:28.811  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, you should have been a doctor?

540
00:30:32.730 --> 00:30:35.496  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Your bandage will need to be changed soon.

541
00:30:35.569 --> 00:30:40.128  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I think I'd like a blue
chiffon bandage this time,

542
00:30:40.207 --> 00:30:41.807  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
maybe some rhinestones.

543
00:30:41.887 --> 00:30:43.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Something with a little pizazz.

544
00:30:43.486 --> 00:30:45.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is no joking matter.

545
00:30:45.868 --> 00:30:46.245  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You are seriously injured,

546
00:30:46.326 --> 00:30:47.765  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and we have
a great deal of terrain to cover.

547
00:30:48.126 --> 00:30:50.325  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just trying to lighten the mood.

548
00:30:50.405 --> 00:30:52.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is neither the time nor the place.

549
00:30:52.604 --> 00:30:54.683  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened to that new Worf?

550
00:30:54.763 --> 00:30:56.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, the one with the sense of humor?

551
00:30:57.802 --> 00:30:59.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That was a mistake.

552
00:30:59.562 --> 00:31:01.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, what is that supposed to mean?

553
00:31:01.601 --> 00:31:03.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It means if I had
not been joking with you,

554
00:31:03.520 --> 00:31:06.200  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I would not have allowed
the Jem'Hadar to get so close.

555
00:31:06.280 --> 00:31:08.719  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs ) So this is all my fault.

556
00:31:08.799 --> 00:31:10.199  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

557
00:31:10.279 --> 00:31:11.678  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is mine.

558
00:31:12.318 --> 00:31:14.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I was trying to be something I am not.

559
00:31:14.837 --> 00:31:17.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
By letting down my guard,
by ignoring my duty,

560
00:31:17.356 --> 00:31:19.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I allowed my wife to be injured,

561
00:31:19.275 --> 00:31:21.555  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I put the entire mission in jeopardy.

562
00:31:22.395 --> 00:31:23.834  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It will not happen again.

563
00:31:24.354 --> 00:31:25.794  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's not what happened.

564
00:31:26.833 --> 00:31:30.272  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Without our tricorders, there's no way--
-I do not wish to debate this.

565
00:31:32.272 --> 00:31:34.791  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We have a long way to go
and very little time.

566
00:31:35.631 --> 00:31:36.911  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine. Let's go.

567
00:31:37.591 --> 00:31:38.630  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunts )

568
00:32:04.702 --> 00:32:05.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( device beeping )

569
00:32:12.660 --> 00:32:13.739  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ready?

570
00:32:14.500 --> 00:32:15.939  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( softly ) Yeah.

571
00:32:38.332 --> 00:32:39.652  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

572
00:32:52.488 --> 00:32:53.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

573
00:32:59.366 --> 00:33:00.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hypo.

574
00:33:07.603 --> 00:33:08.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groaning )

575
00:33:10.283 --> 00:33:12.602  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There. Good as new.

576
00:33:18.840 --> 00:33:20.840  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have to change your dressing.

577
00:33:20.919 --> 00:33:24.788  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's four bandages in two hours.

578
00:33:24.518 --> 00:33:26.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's got to be some kind of record.

579
00:33:26.957 --> 00:33:30.956  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, sorry. I forgot the new rules.
Nothing funny.

580
00:33:31.365 --> 00:33:32.476  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Got to be serious.

581
00:33:32.556 --> 00:33:34.276  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Life and death.

582
00:33:34.355 --> 00:33:35.915  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We've got a job to do.

583
00:33:39.314 --> 00:33:41.673  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia, I know you are tired,

584
00:33:41.753 --> 00:33:45.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but we have to cover three kilometers
before nightfall. Can you do it?

585
00:33:46.432 --> 00:33:48.552  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As long as you got those painkillers,

586
00:33:48.631 --> 00:33:51.303  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'll follow you
through the gates of hell, sir.

587
00:33:52.470 --> 00:33:53.270  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hmm...

588
00:33:53.350 --> 00:33:56.269  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, that was almost a smile.

589
00:33:59.788 --> 00:34:03.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When this mission is over,
I will smile all you want.

590
00:34:04.272 --> 00:34:05.426  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, you promise?

591
00:34:06.665 --> 00:34:07.345  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I promise.

592
00:34:08.985 --> 00:34:12.644  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Then let's finish this mission
and get out of here.

593
00:34:14.634 --> 00:34:15.543  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( both grunt )

594
00:34:15.623 --> 00:34:17.142  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoa.

595
00:34:17.222 --> 00:34:18.222  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( groans )

596
00:34:18.303 --> 00:34:19.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's all right, I can stand.

597
00:34:19.862 --> 00:34:21.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just help me get my balance.

598
00:34:21.221 --> 00:34:22.581  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Help me balance.

599
00:34:23.381 --> 00:34:24.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or maybe not.

600
00:34:25.301 --> 00:34:26.660  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( gasps )

601
00:34:29.858 --> 00:34:31.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( grunting )

602
00:34:36.572 --> 00:34:37.217  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beeping )

603
00:34:39.575 --> 00:34:42.695  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Let me guess. Things aren't looking up.

604
00:34:43.175 --> 00:34:45.175  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
There's been another drop
in your blood pressure.

605
00:34:45.254 --> 00:34:47.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And your neural E.D.L. readings
are erratic.

606
00:34:48.174 --> 00:34:50.613  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what's your prescription, doc?

607
00:34:51.692 --> 00:34:54.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Surgery... at a Starbase.

608
00:34:54.131 --> 00:34:56.570  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could I get a second opinion?

609
00:35:03.369 --> 00:35:06.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf, you have to go on without me...

610
00:35:07.447 --> 00:35:08.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And I know that.

611
00:35:08.847 --> 00:35:10.407  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand.

612
00:35:10.487 --> 00:35:12.926  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My duty requires
that I complete the mission

613
00:35:13.669 --> 00:35:14.646  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
regardless of my personal feelings.

614
00:35:15.245 --> 00:35:16.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Absolutely.

615
00:35:16.365 --> 00:35:18.852  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're a Starfleet officer.

616
00:35:18.164 --> 00:35:20.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So am I, and I understand.

617
00:35:21.365 --> 00:35:24.962  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The information Lasaran has could be
potentially invaluable to the war effort.

618
00:35:25.428 --> 00:35:27.642  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You don't have to explain to me.

619
00:35:28.121 --> 00:35:29.880  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm hurt. You're not.

620
00:35:30.681 --> 00:35:32.920  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And there's a job to be done.

621
00:35:33.539 --> 00:35:34.439  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will be back tomorrow night.

622
00:35:36.319 --> 00:35:37.799  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't worry.

623
00:35:37.878 --> 00:35:39.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not going anywhere.

624
00:35:39.958 --> 00:35:43.437  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can have you in the stasis chamber
on the runabout in 45 hours.

625
00:35:44.916 --> 00:35:46.195  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No problem.

626
00:35:47.116 --> 00:35:48.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I will leave the med kit.

627
00:35:48.675 --> 00:35:51.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Scan yourself with the tricorder
every half hour.

628
00:35:51.274 --> 00:35:52.954  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The plasma hypospray will be set--

629
00:35:53.514 --> 00:35:56.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I took basic first aid.
I know what I have to do.

630
00:36:01.231 --> 00:36:02.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Worf.

631
00:36:04.230 --> 00:36:06.750  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's been a great two months, hasn't it?

632
00:36:10.688 --> 00:36:11.688  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

633
00:36:14.787 --> 00:36:18.264  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jadzia, I just want to tell you how--

634
00:36:19.667 --> 00:36:20.745  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( whispers ) Just kiss me and go.

635
00:36:42.859 --> 00:36:43.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sobbing )

636
00:36:59.254 --> 00:37:01.533  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( heart beating )

637
00:37:13.250 --> 00:37:16.129  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( beating louder )

638
00:37:41.641 --> 00:37:42.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

639
00:38:03.874 --> 00:38:05.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What's the word?

640
00:38:08.793 --> 00:38:10.553  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She is still in surgery,

641
00:38:10.633 --> 00:38:13.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but Dr. Bashir is hopeful
she will make a full recovery.

642
00:38:14.871 --> 00:38:15.991  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lasaran's dead.

643
00:38:16.711 --> 00:38:18.310  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Starfleet intelligence
intercepted a transmission

644
00:38:18.390 --> 00:38:21.909  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
saying that he'd been killed
trying to reenter the base at Soukara.

645
00:38:21.989 --> 00:38:23.868  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Could you have made the rendezvous?

646
00:38:23.949 --> 00:38:25.690  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

647
00:38:25.748 --> 00:38:28.267  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-But yet you turned back to save Jadzia.
-Yes.

648
00:38:28.547 --> 00:38:30.507  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Were you aware that
the information that man had

649
00:38:30.586 --> 00:38:32.586  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
could have saved millions of lives?

650
00:38:33.506 --> 00:38:34.546  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes.

651
00:38:34.985 --> 00:38:36.225  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So what happened?

652
00:38:37.705 --> 00:38:40.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You may not understand.
-Try me, sir.

653
00:38:43.103 --> 00:38:44.663  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You were at my wedding.

654
00:38:44.742 --> 00:38:46.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You heard the story
of the first two Klingon hearts

655
00:38:47.618 --> 00:38:48.741  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and how nothing could stand against them

656
00:38:48.821 --> 00:38:51.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and how they even destroyed
the Gods that had created them.

657
00:38:52.420 --> 00:38:54.980  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have heard that story since I was a boy,

658
00:38:55.539 --> 00:38:57.379  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
but I never understood it...

659
00:38:57.458 --> 00:38:59.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I mean really understood it...

660
00:39:00.980 --> 00:39:03.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Until I was standing in the jungle
with my heart pounding in my chest,

661
00:39:03.776 --> 00:39:07.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and I found that even I could
not stand against my own heart.

662
00:39:07.655 --> 00:39:09.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I had to go back.

663
00:39:10.255 --> 00:39:11.854  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And it did not matter
what Starfleet thought,

664
00:39:11.934 --> 00:39:13.214  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
or what the consequences were.

665
00:39:13.294 --> 00:39:16.938  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was my wife and I could not leave her.

666
00:39:17.293 --> 00:39:20.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
As your captain,
it is my duty to inform you

667
00:39:20.292 --> 00:39:22.331  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
that you made the wrong choice.

668
00:39:23.650 --> 00:39:26.410  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't think Starfleet will file
any formal charges.

669
00:39:27.330 --> 00:39:29.289  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Even a secret court-martial
would run the risk

670
00:39:29.369 --> 00:39:32.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of revealing too much about
their intelligence operations.

671
00:39:33.608 --> 00:39:36.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this will go into your service record.

672
00:39:37.766 --> 00:39:40.525  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And to be completely honest,

673
00:39:40.606 --> 00:39:44.846  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
you probably won't be offered
a command on your own after this.

674
00:39:46.411 --> 00:39:47.204  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I understand.

675
00:39:47.284 --> 00:39:49.523  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've also issued new orders.

676
00:39:49.603 --> 00:39:51.723  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You and Jadzia are not
to be assigned to a mission

677
00:39:51.802 --> 00:39:53.801  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
on your own ever again.

678
00:39:58.880 --> 00:40:00.600  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And one last thing.

679
00:40:01.799 --> 00:40:03.879  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As a man who had a wife...

680
00:40:05.878 --> 00:40:08.557  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If Jennifer had been
lying in that clearing...

681
00:40:09.797 --> 00:40:11.916  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I wouldn't have left her either.

682
00:40:17.915 --> 00:40:19.194  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( door opens )

683
00:40:38.108 --> 00:40:39.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey.

684
00:40:40.307 --> 00:40:41.628  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( whispers ) I know you.

685
00:40:42.947 --> 00:40:44.107  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We have met.

686
00:40:44.826 --> 00:40:46.786  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Ah, you're joking again.

687
00:40:47.425 --> 00:40:48.906  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a good sign.

688
00:40:49.985 --> 00:40:51.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Did you make the rendezvous?

689
00:40:53.183 --> 00:40:54.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No.

690
00:40:56.238 --> 00:40:57.862  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( softly) I could not leave you there.

691
00:40:58.902 --> 00:41:02.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not for Lasaran, not for the mission,
not for anything else.

692
00:41:03.740 --> 00:41:05.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Lasaran?

693
00:41:06.980 --> 00:41:08.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dead.

694
00:41:09.197 --> 00:41:10.618  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Are you in trouble?

695
00:41:10.699 --> 00:41:12.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have been in trouble before.

696
00:41:13.538 --> 00:41:15.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm sorry.

697
00:41:15.737 --> 00:41:17.336  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I should have kept going.

698
00:41:17.977 --> 00:41:20.296  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You have nothing to be sorry about.

699
00:41:21.735 --> 00:41:24.215  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know how much your career means to you.

700
00:41:25.951 --> 00:41:26.574  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You come first.

701
00:41:27.294 --> 00:41:30.772  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Before career, before duty,
before anything.

702
00:41:31.972 --> 00:41:34.171  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do not regret what I did,

703
00:41:35.811 --> 00:41:37.691  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and I would do it again.

704
00:41:39.290 --> 00:41:41.209  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't know what to say.

705
00:41:42.769 --> 00:41:46.248  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You could say,
"Thank you for saving my life."

706
00:41:48.487 --> 00:41:50.527  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you for saving my life.

707
00:41:51.446 --> 00:41:54.446  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you could say,
"I would do the same for you, Worf."

708
00:41:55.285 --> 00:41:58.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Well... I'd have to think about that.

709
00:41:59.604 --> 00:42:02.363  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
My career is very important to me,
you know.

710
00:42:03.362 --> 00:42:05.482  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
( sighs )

711
00:42:07.521 --> 00:42:09.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And you could say, "I love you."

712
00:42:13.120 --> 00:42:14.919  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
